OL,4,CUndercover policing: Officer defends
OL,5,Cspying on anti-apartheid movement
OL,6, An undercover officer who spied on the
OL,7, anti-apartheid movement has told an
OL,8, inquiry his work was justified because
OL,9, it could have caused more disorder than
OL,10, the far right.
OL,12,FThe retired officer said its actions,
OL,13,Fin the 1970s, included demonstrations
OL,14,Fagainst cricket and rugby tours.
OL,16,FThe movement caused "problems and
OL,17,Fdangers" and was a "nuisance", he said.
OL,19,FThe elderly officer is the first to
OL,20,Fgive evidence at the Undercover
OL,21,FPolicing Inquiry.
